      • makeSessionsReloadable

        public Map<String,SessionState> makeSessionsReloadable(Set<ObjectName> sessionObjectNames)
        Description copied from interface: ApplicationConfigurationMXBeanSpecific
        This operation will make the specified sessions 'reloadable' from a configuration model point of view. A session is reloadable if it's 'blocked', 'logged off' and it's session manager inactive. To make sure the sessions can be restored to their previous state, a map with the state for each session before the enabling for reload is returned.
        Specified by:
        makeSessionsReloadable in interface ApplicationConfigurationMXBeanSpecific
        Parameters:
        sessionObjectNames - - A set of names of all sessions to make reloadable
        Returns:
        A summary report keyed by session id, with the values of session state before enabling the sessions for reload. The map only contains sessions which were actually affected.
        See Also:
        ApplicationConfigurationMXBeanSpecific.restoreSessionStates(Map)
